    <meta property="og:description" content="Lithium dendrite growth in solid-state electrolytes is a significant challenge for next-generation battery development. Here, authors used dark-field X-ray microscopy to investigate dislocations near dendrite tips, suggesting that stress-induced dislocation may influence dendrite branching and material fracture."/>
